HEADWORD: Frankfort black
<hw>Frank"fort black`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A black pigment used in
copperplate printing, prepared by burning vine twigs, the lees of wine,
etc.</def> <rj><au>McElrath.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

